tar command:
=============
    Create a tar archive: tar -cvf archive.tar file1.txt file2.txt directory
    Extract files from a tar archive: tar -xvf archive.tar


zip and unzip command:
=======================
      Create a zip archive: zip archive.zip file1.txt file2.txt directory
    Extract files from a zip archive: unzip archive.zip


gzip and gunzip command
========================

gzip: The gzip command is used to compress files. It replaces the original file with a compressed version having the .gz extension. For example:

    Compress a file: gzip myfile.txt
    Compress multiple files: gzip file1.txt file2.txt

gunzip: The gunzip command is used to decompress files compressed with gzip. It restores the original file from its compressed version. For example:

    Decompress a file: gunzip myfile.txt.gz
    Decompress multiple files: gunzip file1.txt.gz file2.txt.gz
